Problem.Description:
One day ,ZengBin is learning poem.He saw a love poem writing as:
If you were a teardrop;
In my eye,
For fear of losing you,
I would never cry,
And if the golden sun,
Should cease to shine its light,
Just one smile from you,
Would make my whole world bright.
 ZengBin thinks the poem is so beautiful that he can't forget it.So in order to forget it,he wrote a poem by himself:
no zuo no die why you try,
no try no high give me five,
no zuo no die why you try,
you try you die don't ask why,
why try why high can't be shy
you shy you cry still go die
When ZengBin ends writing this,there are one million "Agimadei" running in his heart(To general,do you know what is "Agimadei",this is something like "Umh..","Aha.."in English or "Yameidei" in Japanese). To celebrate, he decide to help ZhuGe make the problem in this friendly contest,what ZengBin thinks is that:
There is an array A,elements in it like this:
A[i]=F[i]*(Base^C[i]) (^means Base to the power of C[i])
Problem.InputSpec:
There are multiple cases.
In the first line,there is one integer Base which is mentioned above.
In the second line,we give you two integers N and M,N is the size of array A,M is the number of query,
Then there will be one line which has N integers,means the array F
Then there will be one line which has N integers,means the array C
The next M lines has there types,the first integer will always be type.
1.If type=0 , there follows an integer X,you will reverse the value of F[X](that means if F[x]=-1,then F[x]=1,else F[x]=-1);
2.If type=1,there follows two integers X,T,which means add T to values of C[X];
3.If type=2,there follows two integers L,R,you must output the whole multiple of A between L and R(means that A[L]*A[L+1]*...*A[R])mod 20141027 ;

Constraints:
1.Base:[2,100]
2.N:[1,100000],M:[1,100000]
3.F[i]=1 or -1, i is in [1,N]
4.C[i] :[0,100],i is in[1,N]
5.X,L,R:[1,N]
6.T:[0,10]
Problem.OutputSpec:
<FONT size="5">
For each type 2,output the answer,please be careful;
</FONT>
